data.title: Top 20 Worship Songs of 2013
data.meta_description: Six months ago we released our top songs of 2013 (so far).
data.text:
Six months ago we released our top songs of 2013 (so far). In it we made some predictions and discovered some of our favorite songs for congregational worship. Since then we have seen releases from new bands such as The Digital Age and worship standards such as Matt Redman. So here we have compiled the year in songs. There are many more out there and there are likely many songs serving your communities that we have never heard of. Make sure you fill us in with the comments below.

Congregational Songs (on a project released in 2013)

20. “Crown Him (Majesty)”

Burning Lights | Chris Tomlin

Writers: Chris Tomlin, Matt Maher, ED Cash, George Job Elvey, Godfrey Thring, Matthew Bridges
